    "cost_formula_latex": "varies",
    "notes": "Vandermonde matrix; cost = len(x)*(N-1).",
    "summary": "Generate a Vandermonde matrix.",
    "signature": "we.vander(x, N=None, increasing=False)"
  },
  "docs": {
    "sections": [
      {
        "kind": "summary",
        "title": "Summary",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "Generate a Vandermonde matrix."
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "The columns of the output matrix are powers of the input vector. The\norder of the powers is determined by the `increasing` boolean argument.\nSpecifically, when `increasing` is False, the `i`-th output column is\nthe input vector raised element-wise to the power of ``N - i - 1``. Such\na matrix with a geometric progression in each row is named for Alexandre-\nTheophile Vandermonde."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "parameters",
        "title": "Parameters",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "x",
            "type": "array_like",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "1-D input array."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "N",
            "type": "int, optional",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Number of columns in the output.  If `N` is not specified, a square\narray is returned (``N = len(x)``)."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "name": "increasing",
            "type": "bool, optional",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Order of the powers of the columns.  If True, the powers increase\nfrom left to right, if False (the default) they are reversed."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "returns",
        "title": "Returns",
        "items": [
          {
            "name": "out",
            "type": "ndarray",
            "desc_blocks": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "text": "Vandermonde matrix.  If `increasing` is False, the first column is\n``x^(N-1)``, the second ``x^(N-2)`` and so forth. If `increasing` is\nTrue, the columns are ``x^0, x^1, ..., x^(N-1)``."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "kind": "examples",
        "title": "Examples",
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> import numpy as np\n>>> x = np.array([1, 2, 3, 5])\n>>> N = 3\n>>> np.vander(x, N)\narray([[ 1,  1,  1],\n       [ 4,  2,  1],\n       [ 9,  3,  1],\n       [25,  5,  1]])"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> np.column_stack([x**(N-1-i) for i in range(N)])\narray([[ 1,  1,  1],\n       [ 4,  2,  1],\n       [ 9,  3,  1],\n       [25,  5,  1]])"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> x = np.array([1, 2, 3, 5])\n>>> np.vander(x)\narray([[  1,   1,   1,   1],\n       [  8,   4,   2,   1],\n       [ 27,   9,   3,   1],\n       [125,  25,   5,   1]])\n>>> np.vander(x, increasing=True)\narray([[  1,   1,   1,   1],\n       [  1,   2,   4,   8],\n       [  1,   3,   9,  27],\n       [  1,   5,  25, 125]])"
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "text": "The determinant of a square Vandermonde matrix is the product\nof the differences between the values of the input vector:"
          },
          {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "text",
            "code": ">>> np.linalg.det(np.vander(x))\n48.000000000000043 # may vary\n>>> (5-3)*(5-2)*(5-1)*(3-2)*(3-1)*(2-1)\n48"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
